    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Plates, usually metal and either discs or rectangular in shape, decorated or inscribed, and surmounted on a pole to be used in sports shooting as a target pointer, an indicator of where the marksman was to stand, and to be carried in processions of archery or shooting clubs.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
